      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "This looks ideal for ORION THE HUNTER (5). Led and was run down by ATLANTIC OCEAN when fresh but fitter again and meets him 2.5kg better this time. Small field suits and can turn the tables. ATLANTIC OCEAN (3) has been in good form and broke through for a deserved win last time when sweeping home. Retains the claim and although meets the runner-up worse at weights can go close again. FIELD OF FLUTES (2) resumes and looks the main threat to that pair. Strong record course and distance and while fresh. AWASH (4) is back from a let-up and this trip is much sharper than what he's used to but will be doing best work late. DEVILS DELIGHT (1) is a speedy type with a great record course and distance so a solid return wouldn't surprise.",
